  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mine/ERW Risk Education  ERW Survey and Spot Clearance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Three decades of armed conflict in Afghanistan have left widespread mine and ERW contamination across the country.  The current conflict in seven provinces of Kandahar, Urozgan, Zabul, Helmand, Nangarhar, Kunar, and Laghman created problem to all gender type of the residents includes men, women, girls, boys, and mine/ERW amp conflict victims, a huge percentage of the mentioned population have been displaced and fled their hometown, the number of casualties have been increased. 

Since OMAR MRE, demining and Survey/EOD teams are currently working in Kandahar, Helmand, and Nangarhar provinces, the assessment done by our field personnel shows that some of the most at-risk communities from mines and ERW contamination at the moment are living in the provinces of Kandahar, Urozgan, Helmand, Nimroz, Zabul, Laghman, Kunar, and Nangarhar provinces.  The assessment of the communities at risk also took into consideration and shows that the rising number of civilian casualties in the provinces.  This displacement caused to loss their basic right of health, sanitation water, food, school for children, women right, gender equality, and so on.
To mitigate the threat that poses to the lives and livelihoods of civilians, the tool used to do this is mine and ERW risk education and elimination of ERW.
Implementation of this project in mentioned location which is the provision of risk education in IDP camps and host communities,  and elimination of spot ERW to affected population not only prevent further disability by mine/ERW, but also will change their behavior to live in a peaceful environment accepting each other.</narrative>
  </description>
